text: ¬†@ARJUNA JEE (shorts)¬† I never said we can't. But if we close our eyes and say we are doing great even we arnt, then obviously we won't. There are changes that has to be made. India has potential to be bigger than china. But there's some issues which needs to be solved. I mean really big issues which indians dont consider an issue. We are proud of certain wrong doings. Religion, caste, language and many more such things had to be considered secondary. Even right now we are doing same. A country involved in such things never made big. World is an example. Russia had issues with linguistics and islamic world with religion. Let's accept that they will never progress. In the same way, our future is in our hands.
author: KS G

text: ¬†@KS G¬† religions and languages and other traditions must thrive. That‚Äôs the glory of this subcontinent. It will be our soft power. It will be our identity that distinguishes us on this globe. We shouldn‚Äôt take it as a baggage. Caste is a dying issue. Legally there is no caste system in this nation. Caste discrimination is also punishable by law. Ofc discrimination exists but as the newer generation keeps rising the caste discrimination is also slowly wearing away over the years and it‚Äôs happening faster in the urban than in the rural areas. All we must do is not rekindle the caste system and resurrect it. Pretty sure our system will never support another advent of caste discrimination and we must make it fade away surely and completely.
